text: Admir Džubur (13 June 1964 – 23 November 2020) was a Bosnian businessman and football administrator. He was the president of Bosnian Premier League club Željezničar from 29 June 2019 until his death. He was born in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina. Džubur was a Muslim. He was also the director of KJKP "Toplane - Sarajevo". Džubur died on 23 November 2020 from COVID-19, during its pandemic in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina at the age of 56. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Bosnia and Herzegovina Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina businesspeople
title: Admir Džubur
